com.google.appengine.tools.mapreduce.outputs

Class GoogleCloudStorageFileOutput

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.appengine.tools.mapreduce.Output<ByteBuffer,GoogleCloudStorageFileSet>
      • com.google.appengine.tools.mapreduce.outputs.GoogleCloudStorageFileOutput
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class GoogleCloudStorageFileOutput
extends Output<ByteBuffer,GoogleCloudStorageFileSet>
    An Output that writes bytes to a set of Cloud Storage files, one per shard. Produces a single file output (usually on a per-shard basis). This format does not insert any separator characters, so it by default cannot be read back with the CloudStorageLineInputReader.
    See Also:

      • GoogleCloudStorageFileOutput

        public GoogleCloudStorageFileOutput(String bucket,
                            String fileNamePattern,
                            String mimeType,
                            boolean supportSliceRetries)
        Creates output files who's names follow the provided pattern in the specified bucket.
        Parameters:
        fileNamePattern - a Java format string Formatter containing one int argument for the shard number.
        mimeType - The string to be passed as the mimeType to GCS.
        supportSliceRetries - indicates if slice retries should be supported by this writer. Slice retries are achieved by writing each slice to a temporary file and copying it to its destination when processing the next slice.
